        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 9 at 4:05PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 405 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 14 miles west of Hardin to 9 miles
northeast of Fort Smith, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph, occasional lightning and brief
moderate rainfall.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Hardin, Crow Agency, Fort Smith, St. Xavier and Crow Indian
Reservation.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
